Package map

Class Map

java.lang.Object
map.Map
public class Map extends Object
Reads and stores the level data for one map file. The game map is stored in a two-dimensional integer array which contains tile data and positions. Each position in this array contains an integer which corresponds to a specific tile. Another two-dimensional array stores the type and location of objects and entity . Also stores data for level name, size of the map, start and gate locations, number of objects and entities and the number of required keys to move on to the next level. Used to draw and set objects, entities and tiles. Must be instantiated within MapManager to be used in GamePanel and other classes within it.
Author:
Andrew Hein (ach17), Jeffrey Jin (jjj9)

    • Map

      protected Map(GamePanel gp, String mapFile)
      Constructs a new Map object and loads the mapFile. Links gp and TileManager singleton to this class. Loads mapFile; saves data to classes attributes.
      Parameters:
      gp - GamePanel object that is used to run the game
      mapFile - The name of the map file

  • Method Details

    • drawTiles

      protected void drawTiles(Graphics2D graphic2)
      Reads through the two-dimensional tile array and draws tiles corresponding to their tile number in TileManager. Only draws tiles that are currently visible to the player.
      Parameters:
      graphic2 - the main graphics object used to draw sprites on the screen

    • setObject

      protected void setObject()
      Reads the data from the two-dimensional object map array and creates objects corresponding to their object number in ObjectManager. Sets their spawn location to their location in the object map array. If the object is an egg, a random number generator is used to only spawn the eggs 50% of the time. The location of the exit gate is also saved to a variable.
      See Also:
      • OBJ_Egg
      • OBJ_Gate

    • setFarmer

      protected void setFarmer()
      Uses the read information about the map from earlier to determine where to place Farmers on the map. Creates a new farmer and sets their starting location.

    • drawObjects

      protected void drawObjects(Graphics2D graphic2)
      Reads the objects array and draws each object corresponding to their object numbers in ObjectManager. Calls update method in OBJ_Egg every time this method is called.
      Parameters:
      graphic2 - the main graphics object used to draw sprites onto the screen

    • drawFarmers

      protected void drawFarmers(Graphics2D graphic2)

      Parameters:
